===Etymology===
From Ancient Greek prefix ''[[πολυ-]]'', [[poly-]], from ''[[πολύς]]'' (polys), a lot, many + ''[[νήσος]]'' (nesos), island; according to Moon Handbooks Tahiti, "the term Polynesia was coined by Charles de Brosses in 1756 and applied to all the Pacific islands.  The present restricted use was proposed by Dumont d'Urville during a famous lecture at the Geographical Society in Paris in 1831."

